        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>grooving planes [300023803], planes (tools) [300023801], tools for wood-cutting and -finishing [300162913], woodworking tools [300163324], woodworking equipment [300163322], equipment by material processed [300168082], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wide planes with a rabbet taken out of one side and a blade that cuts flush with the rabbet; used for cutting wide bands of particular depths, the depth determined by the depth of the rabbet and the width determined by the width of the blade.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027341/Mercer, Ancient Carpenters' Tools (1960)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Brede schaven met een groef in één kant en een beitel die in hetzelfde vlak als de groef schaaft. Worden gebruikt voor het snijden van brede banden met een bepaalde diepte, waarbij de diepte wordt bepaald door de diepte van de groef en de breedte door de breedte van de beitel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052376/Van Dale hedendaags Nederlands (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>寬形鉋，一邊可取出嵌槽，並有刀片，其切割高度與嵌槽齊平；用於切割特定深度的寬帶，其深淺取決於嵌槽之深度，而寬窄則取決於刀片之寬度。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
